<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,494,1239,1265]" box="[189,494,1239,1265]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,494,1239,1265]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,494,1239,1265]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1287,1351]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Only known from the forests in Kapahiang Regency in 
<collectingRegion box="[872,986,1287,1313]" country="Indonesia" name="Bengkulu" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Bengkulu</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1006,1082,1287,1314]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[207,1380,627,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[207,1380,626,1924]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 4. Map of Sumatra showing the full known species distributions based on collection localities. Each point may represent more than one collection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3805829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3805829/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Found growing in small colonies by the roadside, near a damp ditch in the shade of other herbs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,437,1392,1418]" box="[189,437,1392,1418]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,437,1392,1418]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,437,1392,1418]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1441,1542]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
The fact that this species has some ability to cope with secondary habitats may make it less likely to become threatened. However it is only known from one locality, and hence is best considered as Vulnerable under VUD2 (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[492,633,1515,1541]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref18379" refString="IUCN 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second Edition. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK." type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
) as the only known locality is not in a gazetted protected area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
